To enbale the flush cron job the docker-compose.override.yml should mount the following volumes:

postgis_backups:
   # run annotation flush with cron
   volumes:
     - ./config/postgres/flush.sh:/flush.sh
     - ./config/postgres/flush-cron:/etc/cron.d/backups-cron

Be carefull to set the owner of the file ./config/postgres/flush-cron to root (required for cron jobs) and cannot be fixed in git.

Command:
chown root:root ./config/postgres/flush-cron

